Kenyan champions brace for North Africa opponents‘K’Ogalo’ play CR Belouizdad in first round match of CAF tournament on Wednesday Posta Rangers coach Sammy “Pamzo” Omollo will again be Gor Mahia’s stand-in tactician during the team’s CAF Champions League first round match against CR Belouizdad of Algeria on Wednesday.
The 29-time Kenyan Premier League champions are expected to leave the country on Saturday to face their Algerian opponents and the return leg is slated for January 5.



